  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Postpartum haemorrhage is the main cause of maternal mortality. The aim of investigators'
      study was to evaluate the practice of hemostatic surgery (arterial ligation, uterine
      compression or hysterectomy) when the embolization of uterine arteries wasn't be performed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
